Question: What do you like/dislike about public transportation.
Answer:
for the good part, it can save cost and energy. it can also save the trouble of find parking, especially in downtown of big cities, it is always a pain to find parking, leave alone the expensive parking price. in addition, you can also read or watch something while in the bus or sub, which is good for utilizing the time.
for the dislike, first, it provides little flexibility, e.g., it can not arrive at all the places you want to go, and most of the time, you need to catch its schedule, so you need to compromise your own schedule. second, when it is rush hour or the public transportation has limited resources, it would be very crowd.